@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>@ViewData["Title"]</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="~/lib/bootstrap/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="~/css/site.css" asp-append-version="true" />
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container mt-5">
        <h1 class="mb-4">@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

        <p>Your privacy is crucial to us, especially when it comes to sensitive medical information. This privacy policy explains how we handle and protect your personal and medical data when using our healthcare services platform.</p>

        <h2 class="mt-4">1. Information We Collect</h2>
        <p>We collect various types of personal and medical information in connection with your use of our platform, including but not limited to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Personal information (e.g., name, contact details)</li>
            <li>Medical information (e.g., appointment history, professional consultations)</li>
            <li>Usage data (e.g., IP address, browser type)</li>
            <li>Cookies and tracking technologies</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="mt-4">2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>We use your personal and medical information for the following purposes:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>To schedule and manage your consultations</li>
            <li>To ensure accurate and secure medical record-keeping</li>
            <li>To communicate with you about your appointments and consultations</li>
            <li>To comply with legal and healthcare regulations</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="mt-4">3. How We Protect Your Information</h2>
        <p>We implement appropriate security measures, including encryption and secure databases, to protect your personal and medical information from unauthorized access, alteration, or destruction.</p>

        <h2 class="mt-4">4. Your Rights and Choices</h2>
        <p>You have the right to manage your personal and medical information. You can:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Request access to your medical records</li>
            <li>Update your personal information</li>
            <li>Request deletion of your data in accordance with legal regulations</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="mt-4">5. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
        <p>We may update this privacy policy from time to time. Any changes will be communicated through this page, with an updated effective date.</p>

        <h2 class="mt-4">6. Contact Us</h2>
        <p>If you have any questions about this privacy policy or how your information is handled, please contact us at:</p>
        <address>
            <strong>Email:</strong> privacy@webclinica.com<br />
            <strong>Phone:</strong> +1 (123) 456-7890
        </address>
    </div>

    <script src="~/lib/jquery/dist/jquery.min.js"></script>
    <script src="~/lib/bootstrap/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
